.TH "cpufreq_notify_transition" 9 "cpufreq_notify_transition" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpufreq_notify_transition \- Notify frequency transition and adjust jiffies.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cpufreq_notify_transition
.BI "(struct cpufreq_policy *policy "  ","
.BI "struct cpufreq_freqs *freqs "  ","
.BI "unsigned int state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "policy" 12
cpufreq policy to enable fast frequency switching for.
.IP "freqs" 12
contain details of the frequency update.
.IP "state" 12
set to CPUFREQ_PRECHANGE or CPUFREQ_POSTCHANGE.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function calls the transition notifiers and \fBadjust_jiffies\fP.

It is called twice on all CPU frequency changes that have external effects.
